    Southwestern Capital Markets, Inc. -- Personnel          Robert G. Rodriguez President & CEO 							E-Mail: robert@swcap.com 1100 N.W. Loop 410, Suite 700							San Antonio, Texas 78213 (210) 344-9101             										     Mr. Rodriguez has been engaged in the investment banking field since 1979. Additionally, he has served as underwriter or financial advisor to various governmental agencies including: cities, school, counties, universities, water districts and state agencies. His engagements have included general financial planning, debt management, design of bond issues, marketing research and services, economic feasibility studies, public information brochures, formal dealer offering data, direct agency placements, rating agency and municipal bond insurance presentation. 										     Prior to establishing SCM, Mr. Rodriguez was a partner at a regional investment banking firm. He was responsible for the coordination of activities for the State of Texas headquartered in Houston. Since then, he has participated as underwriter or financial advisor in financings totaling over $26 billion. 										     Mr. Rodriguez received his B.B.A. in Finance and International Business from the University of Houston in 1969. In 1972 he received his CMB from Northwestern University. He is registered with the National Association of Securities Dealers, the New York Stock Exchange and other major exchanges.           He currently holds Series 7, 24, 52, 53 and 63 licenses.                      Patricia Y. Rodriguez Vice President 							E-Mail: patricia@swcap.com 4013 Brookview Rd.							Austin, Texas 78722 (512) 472-6345             										     Ms. Rodriguez has extensive experience in state government as a staff member to Texas State Representative Leticia Van de Putte and to the Lt. Governor of Texas Bob Bullock (1994-1997). As a Legislative Analyst with the Lt. Governorís office, she was involved in legislation related to K-12 education, colonias, housing, water and banking issues. 										     Ms. Rodriguez was previously associated with Southwestern Capital Markets, Inc. in Austin at which time her responsibilities included working with state agencies and local governments with their public finance needs. Her specialties include: preparing official statements, quantitative analysis of issuersí financials, water and wastewater infrastructure financing, school finance issues, especially Instructional Facilities Allotment (IFA) and Qualified Zone Academy Bond (QZAB) applications, locating federal and state grant and/or loan money for issuers, preparing applications to Texas Water Development Board and Texas Natural Resources Conservation Commission and monitoring, analyzing and reporting to clients on changes in state and federal legislation and/or agency rule changes. 										     Ms. Rodriguez received her B.A. from Southern Methodist University with a major in Political Science and a double minor in Economics and Latin American Studies. She received her M.P. Aff. from the LBJ School of Public Affairs at the University of Texas at Austin.           She currently holds Series 52 and 63 licenses.                          Dewey Fitzpatrick Senior Vice President 							E-Mail: dewey@swcap.com 5001 LBJ Freeway, PMB 875							Dallas, Texas 75244 (972) 238-9100             										     Mr. Fitzpatrick serves as the director of institutional sales and underwriting for the firm; he also acts in the capacity of investment banker for special projects. Prior to joining Southwestern Capital Markets, Inc. Mr. Fitzpatrick was Vice President of Institutional Sales and Special Projects with SAMCO Capital Markets in Dallas. He has over twenty years experience in the sale and structuring of Municipal Bonds and other fixed income securities. His career includes serving with The First National Bank of Dallas and Alex, Brown & Sons. Mr. Fitzpatrick is manager of Southwestern Capital Marketsí Dallas office. 										     Mr. Fitzpatrick received his BS in Zoology from the University of Oklahoma and his MBA from East Texas State University (now Texas A&M University at Commerce).           He currently holds Series 7, 24, 52, 53, and 63 licenses.                                  Jerry Hill Compliance Officer  E-Mail: jerry@swcap.com Broker Compliance, Inc.							9726 Twin Creek Dr.							Dallas, Texas 75228							(888) 652-6622             										     Ms. Hill has been involved with the brokerage industry since December, 1964, having worked in all areas including new account, dividends, margin, wire operator, secretary, bookkeeping responsibilities, broker, FINOP, and General Securities Principal. 										     From 1984 to 1993 Ms. Hill was Vice President/owner of a broker/dealer firm. She acted as the General Securities Principal and Financial Operations Principal. Duties included all financials, regulatory filings, commission payroll, P & S, and all compliance with the NASD and SEC. 										     In January 1994, Ms. Hill opened a firm to assist brokerage firms in regulatory compliance and financials.           She currently holds Series 63, 7, 24 and 27 licenses.                                   Stephen P. Arnold Vice President - Institutional Equities  E-Mail: stephen@swcap.com 1100 N.W. Loop 410, Suite 700							San Antonio, Texas 78213							(210) 344-9101             										     Mr. Arnold has been a successful investment professional for over 17 years in both fast paced private and public organizations with asset bases ranging in size from $100 million to $13 billion. He has demonstrated strengths in portfolio management, trading, and security analysis and interest rate forecasts. 										     Prior to SCM, Mr. Arnold was a Vice-President and a Trust Investment Officer for Norwest Investment Management & Trust. He was responsible for securities analysis of municipal and corporate bonds and equities, portfolio management and securities trading for trust, advisory and employee benefit accounts. He developed and implemented a portfolio management system to obtain higher returns, reduce return volatility and improve monitoring of compliance issues. Mr. Arnold also was responsible for identifying, quantifying and treating financial market risks. 										     Mr. Arnold received his Bachelor of Science degree in AG Economics from Texas A&M University in 1979.           He currently holds Series 6, 7 and 63 licenses.                                        [ Home ] [ About Us ] [ Personnel ] [ Institutional Services ] [ E-Mail ] [ Links ] [ FAQ ] Southwestern Capital Markets, Inc. 1100 NW Loop 410, Suite 700 -- (210) 344-9101 -- Fax (210) 344-6527			San Antonio, Texas 78213   © 1999, 2000 Southwestern Capital Markets, Inc.			Site Designed by Web Wizard, Inc.			E-Mail Webmaster    www.scmfinancial.com












